alerts.title: High Surf Advisory
regions: Coastal North Bay Including Point Reyes National Seashore
Southern Monterey Bay and Big Sur Coast
alerts.description: ...High Surf Advisory along the coast through Thursday morning... A large long period northwest swell has arrived at the coastal waters and will persist through Thursday morning. Seas of 14 to 16 feet with breaking waves to 20 feet in the surf zone will be possible. ...HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PDT THURSDAY... * WAVES AND SURF...Seas building rapidly from 14 to 16 feet with breaking waves to 20 feet possible in the surf zone. * TIMING...Until 9 am Thursday. * IMPACTS...Beach visitors, surfers, fisherman and others visiting the beaches should be prepared for rapidly building seas with dangerous crashing waves in the surf zone. Sea surface temperatures in the mid 50s will cause hypothermia in a short amount of time. The surf zone has been relatively tranquil and this will be a quick change in surf conditions. Beach and water related fatalities are common but preventable. Dont become a statistic.
